      },
      "lineNbr": 54,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-28T01:34:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Build Step names use |, and have a less-restricted alphabet. LOGDOG_NAMESPACE is a stream name, and uses \u0027/\u0027 and has a restricted alphabet. It\u0027s messy because logdog stream names are mapped to URLs and base64 encoding them is ugly. It may be (but probably is not) worth making a bootstring-like encoding for the logdog url and then allow the stream names to have an unrestricted character set... maybe even changing the separator to \"|\" to match buildbucket semantics.\n\nI\u0027ll add additional comments.",
      "parentUuid": "196659a1_3a2d759b",
